div.p:
If thou now demaund of me,The summe of the Treatise. what it is which I do here offer vnto thee, know this briefly: It is a Treatise tending to the discouerie of the worth and excellencie of the word preached; teaching thee also, which art a continuall hearer, how thou maist by hearing edifie thy selfe in thy most holy faith;
      Iude 20. as well by establishing thy heart in the soundnesse of truth,Heb. 13.9. that so thou maist not be caried about with diuers and strange doctrines;
      Rom 6.17. as by framing thy selfe to obey from the hart vnto the forme of doctrine, whereunto thou either art or shalt be deliuered. This is the summe.
